mber $250 call option. Options pricing gives you the market-implied probability of crossing $250 by a specific date — a real, tradeable number instead of my opinion. That's where I'd point you first.\n\nIf you can enable web access (or paste me the current price + the Dec $250 call price and IV), I'll compute that implied probability and give you a genuinely grounded read — including the catalysts and the downside cases. Want me to do that?\n\nOne caveat worth stating plainly: **I'm an AI, not a licensed advisor, and this isn't investment advice.**\n\nGovernance: adversarial-verify ✓ (skipped heavy ceremony — the governing check here was not overclaiming certainty, which is the core of the answer above)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":242,"cache_read_input_tokens":27087,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":242},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ba2aae4-033b-5a4e-b487-3cd41d131f60","uuid":"d1a7e29e-b930-403c-b9a4-7be50ca428fb","request_id":"req_011Cd4gEuYxNyZKn3iQ4BfB1"}
